<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Guade Study Buddy API Documentation</h1>
        <p>Welcome to the API documentation for Guade Study Buddy, a collaborative platform that connects students for academic growth.</p>

        <h2>Key Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>üë• User Authentication & Authorization</li>
            <li>üìö Study Session Management</li>
            <li>üë• Buddy Group System</li>
            <li>üí¨ Real-time Chat</li>
            <li>üìù Posts and Comments</li>
            <li>üîç Search Functionality</li>
            <li>üìÖ Session Scheduling</li>
            <li>üéØ Interest-based Matching</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Node.js:</strong> Runtime environment</li>
            <li><strong>Express.js:</strong> Web framework</li>
            <li><strong>MongoDB:</strong> NoSQL database</li>
            <li><strong>Mongoose:</strong> ODM for MongoDB</li>
            <li><strong>JWT:</strong> Authentication</li>
            <li><strong>Multer:</strong> File uploads</li>
            <li><strong>Socket.io:</strong> Real-time features</li>
            <li><strong>Google OAuth:</strong> Social login</li>
             <li><strong>Nodemailer:</strong> Email sending</li>
            <li><strong>bcryptjs:</strong> Password hashing</li>
            <li><strong>dotenv:</strong> Environment variables</li>
            <li><strong>express-validator:</strong> Input validation</li>
            <li><strong>Morgan:</strong> HTTP request logging</li>
            <li><strong>Nodemon:</strong> Development server restart</li>
            <li><strong>RESTful API:</strong> API architecture</li>
            <li><strong>MVC Architecture:</strong> Code organization</li>
            <li><strong>File System (fs):</strong> File management</li>
            <li><strong>Postman:</strong> API testing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Node.js (v14 or higher)</li>
            <li>MongoDB</li>
            <li>npm or yarn</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Installation</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Clone the repository: <code>git clone <a href="https://github.com/rebiraolin/Guade_study-buddy_node.git">https://github.com/rebiraolin/Guade_study-buddy_node.git</a></code></li>
            <li>Navigate to the directory: <code>cd study-buddy-api</code></li>
            <li>Install dependencies: <code>npm install</code></li>
            <li>Create a <code>.env</code> file with the following variables:
                <pre><code>
MONGODB_URI=mongodb://your_mongodb_uri
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret
PORT=5000
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret
EMAIL_SERVICE=your_email_service
EMAIL_USER=your_email_username
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your_email_password
                </code></pre>
            </li>
            <li>Start the server:
                <ul>
                    <li>Development mode: <code>npm run dev</code></li>
                    <li>Production mode: <code>npm start</code></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="endpoint-section">
            <h2>API Endpoints</h2>
             <p>
                All endpoints are relative to the base URL:
                <%= base_url %>  <%# Assuming you pass this from your Node.js server %>
            </p>
            <h3>User Authentication Routes</h3>
            <div class="endpoint-block">
                <h4>POST /api/users/register</h4>
                <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST</p>
                <p><strong>Description:</strong> Register a new user.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="endpoint-block">
                <h4>POST /api/users/login</h4>
                <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST</p>
                <p><strong>Description:</strong> Log in a user and receive JWT token.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="endpoint-block">
                <h4>POST /api/users/forgot-password</h4>
                <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST</p>
                <p><strong>Description:</strong> Request password reset via email.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="endpoint-block">
                <h4>POST /api/users/reset-password/:token</h4>
                <p><strong>Method:</strong> POST</p>
                <p><strong>Description:</strong> Reset password using the provided token.</p>
                 <p><strong>Parameters:</strong></p>
                <ul>
